<D>__{susie...!}
<B>__{another angle}
<A>__{as sidney steps up, he grasps at the door of the taxi, trying to hold it open, but susan pulls it shut, catching his fingers in the door. sidney steps back in pain...}
<B>__{taxi}
<A>__{it drives off down sixth avenue.}
<B>__{sidney}
<A>__{nursing the injury to his hand, he looks after the disappearing taxi. as he recovers from the pain, his expression slowly changes to one of thoughtful appraisal. (susan's suspicions maybe of less importance than some other considerations.)}
